Preheat the oven to 200°C and bring a #saucepan{} of @water{for boiling} up to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} in preparation for the noodles. Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into four long strips then chop widthways into roughly 1cm pieces. Pop them on a large #baking tray{}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Halve the @red chilli{1/2} lengthways, deseed then finely chop.

Season the aubergine with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Drizzle with @oil{for roasting}, toss to coat, then roast on the top shelf of the oven until golden, ~{20-25%minutes}. Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{for frying} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} and fry, stirring regularly, until golden all over and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Pop the @honey{15%ml}, @miso paste{15%g}, @tahini{30%g}, @soy sauce{25%ml} and the @water{80%ml}(for the sauce) into a medium #bowl{} and mix together with a #fork{}. Season with pepper. When the aubergine has about 5 mins left in the oven, add the @egg noodle nests{2} to the boiling water and cook for ~{4%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{}, pop back in the pan and drizzle with a little @oil{for the noodles} to stop them from sticking together.

Once the aubergine is out of the oven, stir it into the pan with the chicken. Add the garlic and a pinch of @?red chilli{pinch} (add less if you don't like too much heat). Stir and cook for ~{1%minute}, then add the sauce you just made. Stir to coat, then leave on medium-high heat to bubble for ~{30%seconds}, until slightly reduced.

Add the noodles and half the coriander to the pan with the chicken and aubergine. Toss together to combine until piping hot, then remove from the heat.

Divide the food between your #bowls{}. Sprinkle over the remaining coriander and add another pinch of chilli. Dig in.